Terraform installation:
=======================
step-1:
=======
create a ec2-instance (RedHat Linux)

step-2:
======
connect to ec2 vm using Mobaxterm

step-3:
=======
switch to root user
 $ sudo su -

step-4:
=======
upgrade all packages
 # yum upgrade

step-5:
=======
yum-utils ->The name of the package to install.
 # yum install -y yum-utils

yum-utils is a collection of useful YUM-related tools, such as:
 yum-config-manager
 package-cleanup
 reposync
 debuginfo-install

step-6:
========
yum-related tools
 # yum-config-manager --add-repo https://rpm.releases.hashicorp.com/RHEL/hashicorp.repo

step-7:
=======
install terraform
 # yum -y install terraform

step-8:
=======
check terraform version
 # terraform --version

step-9:
=======
create IAM user with programmatic access and provide "AmazonEc2FullAccess"

step-10:
========
Download Secret key and Access key

step-11:
========
Then Write Terraform script.
